# design-handoff — ⟨PRODUCT_NAME⟩

**patternVersion:** `0.1`  
**Slot:** Recommended (Required for UI-heavy products — mark in MASTER-PLAN adapter).

Place the **approved** design package here (spec, tokens, components, screens, sample data). Agents treat this as design source of truth for UI units; do not invent chrome outside it without Admin + catalog (if UI-catalog is Required).

## Expected contents (example)

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `README.md` | Index / how to use |
| product spec | Intent + flows |
| tokens | Colors / type / spacing |
| components / screens | Inventory |

## Rule

UI blueprints list this directory (or specific files) under Inputs. Diffs that invent unapproved chrome fail audit when the product opts into UI-catalog.
